entries.title: Your Monday Briefing: The Fallout from a Police Beating
entries.description: Also, violence is flaring in Israel and the West Bank.

entries.title: The Hunt for Nazi-Buried Treasure in a Dutch Village
entries.description: The public release of a map from the 1940s has drawn fortune seekers with shovels and metal detectors to a small Dutch village. Not everyone is excited.

entries.title: In the Fight Over Gas Stoves, Meet the Industry’s Go-To Scientist
entries.description: Longstanding research shows the health dangers of gas-burning ranges. Utilities are turning to Julie Goodman, a toxicologist with a firm whose work raises questions about the science.

entries.title: Russia and Ukraine Battle for Control of Villages Near the Key City of Bakhmut
entries.description: The area is a flash point in an offensive that Moscow views as crucial for its goal of seizing the Donbas region of eastern Ukraine.

entries.title: U.K. Prime Minister Ousts Top Party Official
entries.description: In trying to bring “integrity” back to Downing Street, Rishi Sunak fired Nadhim Zahawi, the chairman of the governing Conservatives, over his personal tax affairs.

entries.title: Industry Gatekeepers
entries.description: One company controls a wide swath of the concert industry, and lawmakers say music fans are paying the price.

entries.title: Can K-Pop Make the Metaverse Cool?
entries.description: In the world’s testing ground for tech, K-pop singers are being spun up out of pixels and doing battle in a virtual universe.

entries.title: Palestinian Man Fatally Shot as Violence Continues With Israel Forces
entries.description: Tensions and violence have gripped the Israeli-occupied West Bank and Jerusalem for days after an Israeli military raid on Thursday killed nine people.

entries.title: Bus Plunge in Pakistan Kills at Least 40
entries.description: The vehicle plunged down a ravine while traveling more than 300 miles from Quetta to the port city of Karachi.

entries.title: Iran Says It Thwarted a Drone Attack on a Munitions Facility
entries.description: The government did not say who was behind the attempted attack, but some Telegram channels affiliated with Iran’s Revolutionary Guards pointed the finger at Israel.
